The paper discusses a query suggestion framework for Intranet search, which falls under the Information Retrieval (IR) domain. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of user interaction data, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, making cs.CL a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper focuses on personalisation and user profiling, which are related to human-computer interaction (HCI) and database (DB) domains, respectively. Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to re-rank the query suggestion list, which falls under the machine learning (LG) domain.
